50|$|Previously, all Christian Churches used altar cloths. However, today {{some use}} no cloths {{on the altar}} or only the fair linen. Several {{variants}} of the above <b>cloths</b> and <b>linens</b> are also in use. Some Churches use a frontlet and no frontal, especially where the altar is richly decorated and a frontal would hide it. Where only a frontlet is used, {{in many cases the}} frontlet is permanently attached to the <b>linen</b> <b>cloth,</b> and so the <b>linen</b> <b>cloth</b> must be replaced with the frontlet. Many Churches dispense with the cere cloth and the coverlet.|$|R
