25|$|High Wycombe {{remained}} a mill town through Medieval and Tudor times, manufacturing lace and <b>linen</b> <b>cloth.</b> It {{was also a}} stopping point on the way from Oxford to London, with many travellers staying in the town's taverns and inns.|$|R
50|$|The {{purificator}} (purificatorium or more anciently emunctorium) {{is a white}} <b>linen</b> <b>cloth</b> {{which is}} used to wipe the chalice after each communicant partakes. It is also used to wipe the chalice and paten after the ablutions which follow Communion.|$|R
